values: What kind of a world is it where children turn into skeletons with spindle legs that break if they walk? What kind of a world is it where mothers sell themselves to feed their babies? What kind of a world is it where sons and daughters are left to fend for them selves because their parents are dead? What kind of world is it where corrupt leaders keep money meant to help their people? What kind of a world is it where there is no fresh water to drink or where people stave or where disease spreads like wild fire or where there is no medicine for the sick? What kind of people are we that we can turn our back on suffering, that we cannot make a small effort to help those in extreme need? Do your part support the ONE campaign: Please post this in your blog, on your website, on a telephone pole, anywhere just get the message out there.

I had just sewn buttons onto an awsome suit that I got at salvies for $15 dollars(for DI), and then my dad came over and said something like:

Why is the world so cruel? Is it cruel to walk by a homeless person, with out even giving them a second glance? 

In harvard square last month I think it was I saw a homless man sitting cross legged on a gruby blanket. He had on a ratty coat and he looked like a yogi from India. He was flicking seeds onto the brick and tiny birds gathered around him to eat, while the world just walked by.

At least I'm sad for once, and not just pissed off.
